Hist. 4:1-676] as fast Wuk Series Calls, at 8:25, 9:10 (distant bird in background), and 20:06.  By contrast, series of calls at 8:07-8:26, 9:45-9:53, 10:01-10:05, 10:18-10:21, 10:59, 11:10-11:15, 11:22-11:25, 11:35-11:39, 11:45-11:48, 11:49-11:52, 15:18-15:20, and 15:51-15:53 instead represent the "Wok" Call of Short 1982 (also p. 420).  Tapping is scattered almost throughout recording, with the best examples at 10:35-10:48 and 14:02-14:37, and there is some wing rustling at 18:14-18:16 and 19:26-19:28 when bird made brief flights.  There appear to be "cryptic" stop-starts at 5:26 and 12:57.
